main event: A witness observed 5 to 6 erratic lights moving in the sky over Chicago, Illinois on 20 June 1966 for about 30 seconds.
interesting points: The lights did not appear attached to any conventional aircraft,The witness noted the lights were extremely bright and moved in a southerly direction,The lights flashed at irregular intervals,The sighting is described as having an impression of flying at a rapid speed,The Air Force later suggested that the sightings could be related to an aircraft advertising sign.
sighted object: 5 to 6 bright lights in the sky
witness description: A 57-year-old male who reported observing the lights from his apartment.
